This paper deals with the problem of online community moderation, which falls under the broad category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning for identifying communities at risk of committing offenses, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) or cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of data analysis and modeling, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) or machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of community bans and quarantines on the behavior of members of these communities, which could fall under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL) or software engineering (cs.SE).
